message:
@pevans_om Another note on the "Argumentative Christianity"... I have never seen it as a defense for God. It is me making a defense for my hope (1 Peter 3:15). I also find it helps me solidify what and why I believe. It edifies me when proof is given for the things the Bible claims.

I think there is a weakness when you are asked why you believe X (which seems like hocus pocus to say an atheist) and you cannot give a reason. Because I always thought that? Cause my teacher says so? Cause my church says so?

Personally I don't really care about the age of the earth. That debate has never tickled my fancy though :)
